1
00:01:01,000 --> 00:01:01,680
Thanks.

2
00:01:08,000 --> 00:01:09,760
So can you two tell me

3
00:01:09,760 --> 00:01:11,200
exactly what happened?

4
00:01:12,400 --> 00:01:13,200
It's like this.

5
00:01:13,960 --> 00:01:14,840
Our company

6
00:01:15,160 --> 00:01:17,160
recently took over an abandoned project.

7
00:01:18,360 --> 00:01:19,280
Our boss

8
00:01:19,640 --> 00:01:21,120
wants to rebuild it.

9
00:01:23,760 --> 00:01:24,600
But then,

10
00:01:25,120 --> 00:01:27,320
some strange things started happening.

11
00:01:27,680 --> 00:01:28,120
And...

12
00:01:28,560 --> 00:01:30,160
we can't continue construction.

13
00:01:30,640 --> 00:01:31,440
At the site,

14
00:01:31,680 --> 00:01:32,920
everyone's on edge.

15
00:01:34,000 --> 00:01:34,800
So what

16
00:01:34,800 --> 00:01:36,760
kind of strange things happened?

17
00:01:37,520 --> 00:01:38,320
Well,

18
00:01:39,000 --> 00:01:39,640
at the site,

19
00:01:39,800 --> 00:01:40,720
people kept

20
00:01:40,880 --> 00:01:42,280
getting injured for no reason.

21
00:01:42,840 --> 00:01:43,360
Lately,

22
00:01:43,720 --> 00:01:44,840
it's been getting worse.

23
00:01:44,920 --> 00:01:46,120
Until a couple of days ago,

24
00:01:46,280 --> 00:01:47,760
someone actually saw a ghost.

25
00:01:49,560 --> 00:01:50,960
You mean to say

26
00:01:51,120 --> 00:01:52,600
one of your men saw a ghost?

27
00:01:53,600 --> 00:01:54,280
Old Liu,

28
00:01:54,560 --> 00:01:55,400
tell this young lady

29
00:01:55,400 --> 00:01:56,840
what actually happened.

30
00:01:59,680 --> 00:02:01,240
That night, I

31
00:02:01,720 --> 00:02:03,200
was coming back from my patrol.

32
00:02:19,920 --> 00:02:20,720
Xiaofu

33
00:02:20,920 --> 00:02:22,080
Don't worry

34
00:02:22,240 --> 00:02:23,440
Let's wait a bit longer for big bro

35
00:02:24,960 --> 00:02:26,320
It's already been several days

36
00:02:26,320 --> 00:02:27,560
Are we still doing this job or not?

37
00:02:27,600 --> 00:02:29,160
Why hasn't big bro sent word yet?

38
00:03:22,200 --> 00:03:23,600
So what you're saying is,

39
00:03:23,680 --> 00:03:24,800
you saw a person

40
00:03:24,800 --> 00:03:26,680
who vanished right in front of you?

41
00:03:27,200 --> 00:03:28,320
How should I know?

42
00:03:28,480 --> 00:03:29,520
It scared me so bad, I...

43
00:03:30,000 --> 00:03:30,960
I was shaking all over!

44
00:03:33,920 --> 00:03:35,160
And that's exactly

45
00:03:35,480 --> 00:03:36,840
why we came to find you.

46
00:03:37,400 --> 00:03:38,600
We just want you guys

47
00:03:38,680 --> 00:03:39,640
to help us as soon as possible

48
00:03:39,640 --> 00:03:41,280
to deal with this ghost situation,

49
00:03:41,800 --> 00:03:43,240
so we can get back to work.

50
00:03:44,120 --> 00:03:45,160
Got it, got it.

51
00:03:46,280 --> 00:03:48,720
Construction sites do have heavy yin energy.

52
00:03:48,960 --> 00:03:50,640
But whether there's actually something there,

53
00:03:50,760 --> 00:03:52,920
we'll only know after we take a look.

54
00:03:53,200 --> 00:03:54,000
Okay, okay, okay.

55
00:03:54,000 --> 00:03:55,440
But, um,

56
00:03:55,840 --> 00:03:57,280
I hope you can hurry.

57
00:03:57,400 --> 00:03:58,480
Right, our boss said,

58
00:03:59,120 --> 00:04:00,160
money's not a problem.

59
00:04:00,800 --> 00:04:01,960
The most important thing is speed.

60
00:04:03,120 --> 00:04:03,880
Don't worry, don't worry.

61
00:04:03,880 --> 00:04:05,000
We'll definitely be quick.

62
00:04:05,680 --> 00:04:07,560
Then we'll be on our way.

63
00:04:07,840 --> 00:04:09,160
Okay, okay, take care.

64
00:04:10,080 --> 00:04:11,080
I won't see you out. Thanks!

65
00:04:11,240 --> 00:04:11,920
Don't mention it.

66
00:04:32,480 --> 00:04:33,440
Hello, Lin You.

67
00:04:33,640 --> 00:04:34,760
Where are you guys?

68
00:04:35,120 --> 00:04:36,360
I'm out with Zhou Yi.

69
00:04:36,360 --> 00:04:37,080
What's up?

70
00:04:40,800 --> 00:04:42,720
Then hurry back soon, okay?

71
00:04:42,720 --> 00:04:44,000
I'll tell you when you get back.

72
00:04:44,280 --> 00:04:44,800
Okay.

73
00:04:50,840 --> 00:04:55,360
Then let's do one last thing for Daji.

74
00:05:26,400 --> 00:05:27,200
Zhou Yi

75
00:05:27,840 --> 00:05:28,640
Zhou Yi

76
00:05:30,000 --> 00:05:30,800
Is this...

77
00:05:31,320 --> 00:05:32,880
Is this the method you were talking about?

78
00:05:35,680 --> 00:05:36,640
Of course

79
00:05:37,240 --> 00:05:38,800
I promised to help you build up your nerve

80
00:05:39,400 --> 00:05:41,680
A place like this is perfect for it

81
00:05:43,360 --> 00:05:44,360
Although

82
00:05:44,600 --> 00:05:45,720
this level of scare

83
00:05:45,960 --> 00:05:47,520
I haven't messed with since I was fifteen.

84
00:05:48,320 --> 00:05:49,400
Fifteen?

85
00:05:50,640 --> 00:05:51,240
That's right

86
00:05:51,480 --> 00:05:52,440
Fine, fine

87
00:05:54,240 --> 00:05:55,040
Liu Liu

88
00:05:55,960 --> 00:05:56,760
Liu Liu

89
00:05:58,000 --> 00:05:59,240
Why did you come along?

90
00:05:59,800 --> 00:06:00,440
Me?

91
00:06:00,640 --> 00:06:03,000
I'm here to keep you guys company, obviously

92
00:06:05,640 --> 00:06:08,920
I can't stay overnight with you,

93
00:06:08,920 --> 00:06:09,720
but

94
00:06:09,920 --> 00:06:12,000
I can definitely tag along

95
00:06:12,080 --> 00:06:13,560
to help build up your nerve.

96
00:06:14,800 --> 00:06:15,600
Alright

97
00:06:16,360 --> 00:06:17,800
Then you stay safe out there

98
00:06:35,400 --> 00:06:36,360
That scared me to death!

99
00:06:36,560 --> 00:06:37,480
Scared me to death!

100
00:06:38,400 --> 00:06:39,040
Let's get out of here!

101
00:06:49,280 --> 00:06:50,120
I mean, look at you...

102
00:06:51,240 --> 00:06:52,480
Why do you put yourself through this?

103
00:06:54,440 --> 00:06:58,040
I actually find it kind of thrilling.

104
00:06:59,840 --> 00:07:01,520
But then again...

105
00:07:01,600 --> 00:07:04,200
Do you feel like this every night?

106
00:07:04,920 --> 00:07:05,840
Pretty much.

107
00:07:14,080 --> 00:07:16,680
You've got to learn to face your fears.

108
00:07:17,400 --> 00:07:18,600
Otherwise, always running away

109
00:07:19,320 --> 00:07:20,520
isn't really a solution.

110
00:07:22,840 --> 00:07:23,920
You're really something.

111
00:07:25,000 --> 00:07:26,600
How did your parents even raise you?

112
00:07:26,640 --> 00:07:27,760
How are you this fearless?

113
00:07:29,080 --> 00:07:29,880
Whoa!

114
00:07:32,920 --> 00:07:34,080
My new mask...

115
00:07:34,360 --> 00:07:34,920
What do you think?

116
00:07:37,360 --> 00:07:38,200
Parents?

117
00:07:39,360 --> 00:07:41,160
I don't even know who my parents are.

118
00:07:44,880 --> 00:07:45,680
Then have you...

119
00:07:46,480 --> 00:07:47,800
ever thought about finding them?

120
00:07:54,160 --> 00:07:55,840
I actually asked Lao Wang once

121
00:07:56,080 --> 00:07:57,160
about my parents.

122
00:07:58,840 --> 00:08:00,240
But every time, he'd say

123
00:08:00,520 --> 00:08:02,280
I either fell from a lightning strike,

124
00:08:02,600 --> 00:08:04,400
or I was picked out of a trash can.

125
00:08:06,280 --> 00:08:07,280
And then?

126
00:08:09,560 --> 00:08:10,640
Then...

127
00:08:10,880 --> 00:08:12,120
I just stopped asking.

128
00:08:14,240 --> 00:08:15,680
But it's not hard to figure out.

129
00:08:16,040 --> 00:08:17,040
No matter who they were,

130
00:08:17,760 --> 00:08:18,760
ending up with a kid like me,

131
00:08:18,960 --> 00:08:21,040
born with a heart condition,

132
00:08:22,440 --> 00:08:23,840
anyone would choose to walk away.

133
00:08:25,040 --> 00:08:26,120
That's why you treat Uncle Wang

134
00:08:26,120 --> 00:08:27,240
like your family.

135
00:08:31,720 --> 00:08:33,360
Even though Sister Bai is great to me,

136
00:08:34,200 --> 00:08:36,159
I grew up at Daji.

137
00:08:37,320 --> 00:08:38,280
In my heart,

138
00:08:38,640 --> 00:08:40,039
Daji is my home.

139
00:08:40,679 --> 00:08:43,000
Lao Wang and Sister Bai are my family.

140
00:08:43,520 --> 00:08:44,320
So...

141
00:08:44,600 --> 00:08:45,800
as long as Daji is here,

142
00:08:46,680 --> 00:08:47,560
it seems like

143
00:08:48,160 --> 00:08:50,120
I'm not missing anything others have.

144
00:08:52,840 --> 00:08:53,640
Besides,

145
00:08:53,720 --> 00:08:54,920
you've got us now.

146
00:08:57,080 --> 00:08:58,120
From this day on,

147
00:08:58,280 --> 00:08:59,960
the three of us are

148
00:09:00,280 --> 00:09:02,320
the most in-sync trio ever.

149
00:09:07,600 --> 00:09:08,400
Oh, right.

150
00:09:08,880 --> 00:09:10,080
About that big job earlier,

151
00:09:10,760 --> 00:09:12,320
should we tell Uncle Wang?

152
00:09:13,400 --> 00:09:14,800
I think...

153
00:09:15,520 --> 00:09:16,080
no need.

154
00:09:17,880 --> 00:09:19,160
Listen up, you two.

155
00:09:19,600 --> 00:09:22,040
Lao Wang's birthday is in a couple of days.

156
00:09:22,520 --> 00:09:23,960
That old man is super picky.

157
00:09:24,440 --> 00:09:26,320
You'd better think hard about a gift.

158
00:09:26,960 --> 00:09:27,480
Lin You,

159
00:09:27,960 --> 00:09:28,880
especially you.

160
00:09:28,880 --> 00:09:30,000
Think it through carefully.

161
00:09:41,360 --> 00:09:43,880
If we're done resting,

162
00:09:44,000 --> 00:09:46,280
shall we keep going?

163
00:09:46,280 --> 00:09:47,480
Continue exploring.

164
00:09:48,640 --> 00:09:49,120
Let's go.

165
00:09:49,960 --> 00:09:50,640
Come on, Lin You!

166
00:09:51,640 --> 00:09:52,400
Let's head back.

167
00:09:52,600 --> 00:09:53,480
It's fine.

168
00:10:24,080 --> 00:10:24,760
Lao Wang!

169
00:10:25,520 --> 00:10:26,280
Where are you?

170
00:10:28,400 --> 00:10:29,480
You little brats!

171
00:10:35,800 --> 00:10:37,120
Wishing Lao Wang

172
00:10:37,520 --> 00:10:39,520
a happy birthday!

173
00:10:41,680 --> 00:10:43,880
Let me see what gifts you got me.

174
00:10:45,880 --> 00:10:47,280
Liu Liu's the best.

175
00:10:47,360 --> 00:10:49,680
She always knows what to give.

176
00:10:50,600 --> 00:10:51,280
Alright.

177
00:10:52,920 --> 00:10:54,440
Let's see what you two got me.

178
00:10:55,160 --> 00:10:56,720
Isn't mine pretty good?

179
00:10:57,360 --> 00:10:58,840
Coffin, coffin...

180
00:10:58,840 --> 00:10:59,880
It means promotion and wealth!

181
00:11:00,320 --> 00:11:01,520
You get it?

182
00:11:02,000 --> 00:11:04,120
You give me a coffin for my birthday?

183
00:11:04,280 --> 00:11:05,280
And you're even worse.

184
00:11:05,880 --> 00:11:07,080
Giving me reading glasses?

185
00:11:07,280 --> 00:11:08,320
I'm in my prime!

186
00:11:08,320 --> 00:11:10,280
What's that supposed to mean?

187
00:11:10,480 --> 00:11:12,200
Look at Liu Liu's gift, these shades.

188
00:11:12,200 --> 00:11:13,040
So cool!

189
00:11:13,600 --> 00:11:14,400
Uncle Wang,

190
00:11:14,760 --> 00:11:16,280
your eyesight's already bad.

191
00:11:16,320 --> 00:11:17,680
You can't even draw talismans clearly.

192
00:11:17,680 --> 00:11:18,440
Besides,

193
00:11:18,640 --> 00:11:20,040
they really suit your style.

194
00:11:20,040 --> 00:11:20,840
You... I...

195
00:11:21,000 --> 00:11:22,640
Is that how you talk to your master?

196
00:11:25,760 --> 00:11:27,040
Move, move, move.

197
00:11:27,360 --> 00:11:28,080
Let me tell you,

198
00:11:28,080 --> 00:11:29,040
I'll show you

199
00:11:29,080 --> 00:11:29,880
something real.

200
00:11:29,880 --> 00:11:31,560
Or you'll think I'm just bragging.

201
00:11:31,880 --> 00:11:32,440
Take a look.

202
00:11:33,320 --> 00:11:33,840
Look at this.

203
00:11:34,240 --> 00:11:35,040
Master,

204
00:11:35,160 --> 00:11:36,640
is this you when you were young?

205
00:11:36,840 --> 00:11:37,400
Yep.

206
00:11:38,040 --> 00:11:38,760
I'm telling you,

207
00:11:38,760 --> 00:11:39,840
I was the first person in our village

208
00:11:39,840 --> 00:11:41,480
to ever wear a suit.

209
00:11:43,080 --> 00:11:44,640
That's so cool!

210
00:11:44,640 --> 00:11:45,240
Cool, right?

211
00:11:46,440 --> 00:11:47,040
Kid,

212
00:11:47,600 --> 00:11:48,960
even though you treat your master like that,

213
00:11:49,720 --> 00:11:50,360
still,

214
00:11:50,480 --> 00:11:51,720
I won't shortchange you.

215
00:11:51,720 --> 00:11:53,000
Today's a special day.

216
00:11:53,280 --> 00:11:54,720
I prepared a gift for you.

217
00:11:54,880 --> 00:11:55,440
Over there.

218
00:11:56,360 --> 00:11:57,160
Go check it out.

219
00:12:06,960 --> 00:12:07,600
Kid,

220
00:12:08,320 --> 00:12:09,160
let me tell you,

221
00:12:09,920 --> 00:12:11,120
once you join Daji,

222
00:12:11,240 --> 00:12:12,280
we're all family.

223
00:12:13,280 --> 00:12:14,440
Everyone at Daji

224
00:12:14,440 --> 00:12:16,040
gets their own little potted flower.

225
00:12:16,480 --> 00:12:18,160
This one's yours.

226
00:12:19,000 --> 00:12:21,240
From today on, take good care of it.

227
00:12:21,440 --> 00:12:22,960
If it dies, that's on you.

228
00:12:35,600 --> 00:12:36,400
What's he doing?

229
00:12:37,120 --> 00:12:37,920
Grabbing a pen.

230
00:12:37,920 --> 00:12:38,640
Drawing.

231
00:12:40,520 --> 00:12:41,600
Classic you. Seriously,

232
00:12:41,600 --> 00:12:42,880
you're actually drawing?

233
00:12:44,840 --> 00:12:45,280
Wait,

234
00:12:45,720 --> 00:12:47,200
this is way too ugly.

235
00:12:47,200 --> 00:12:47,920
This, this...

236
00:12:48,520 --> 00:12:49,320
Master,

237
00:12:49,440 --> 00:12:51,680
I think it's drawn pretty well.

238
00:12:52,880 --> 00:12:54,400
So ugly. Be grateful, you two.

239
00:12:54,520 --> 00:12:56,840
In his comics, I'm sometimes a girl,

240
00:12:56,840 --> 00:12:59,320
sometimes a Taoist priest, a fake one too.

241
00:12:59,600 --> 00:13:00,160
And the worst part?

242
00:13:00,400 --> 00:13:01,880
Getting played by a Little Wraith.

243
00:13:02,080 --> 00:13:03,800
You play it better in real life.

244
00:13:04,080 --> 00:13:04,760
Lin You,

245
00:13:05,680 --> 00:13:06,760
thank you.

246
00:13:07,280 --> 00:13:09,360
Guess art really does come from life,

247
00:13:09,440 --> 00:13:10,520
and goes beyond it.

248
00:13:30,240 --> 00:13:31,920
Did you guys find out anything?

249
00:13:36,480 --> 00:13:38,280
I asked around the area,

250
00:13:38,920 --> 00:13:39,920
but I couldn't find

251
00:13:39,920 --> 00:13:41,400
any news about the ghost.

252
00:13:43,120 --> 00:13:43,800
How about

253
00:13:44,000 --> 00:13:46,040
we go ask that old man again?

254
00:14:42,760 --> 00:14:44,200
Big brother said

255
00:14:44,960 --> 00:14:47,000
he can definitely handle it

256
00:14:47,920 --> 00:14:49,720
He told us not to leave yet

257
00:14:50,200 --> 00:14:51,720
Let's just listen to big brother

258
00:14:52,080 --> 00:14:53,400
No problem

259
00:14:54,720 --> 00:14:57,560
But with how things are at the site

260
00:14:58,080 --> 00:15:00,960
isn't it dangerous to keep working?

261
00:15:01,760 --> 00:15:03,200
Quit your whining

262
00:15:03,360 --> 00:15:04,480
Liu Guilan

263
00:15:04,840 --> 00:15:06,440
Big brother said it

264
00:15:06,680 --> 00:15:08,920
If you want money, don't go home

265
00:15:09,320 --> 00:15:10,640
Besides

266
00:15:11,120 --> 00:15:13,440
what kind of man big brother is

267
00:15:13,760 --> 00:15:16,280
don't you all already know?

268
00:15:16,920 --> 00:15:19,280
Just stay

269
00:15:19,920 --> 00:15:22,280
Just stay

270
00:15:24,600 --> 00:15:25,000
This...

271
00:15:27,600 --> 00:15:29,360
There really are ghosts!

272
00:15:31,680 --> 00:15:34,120
It's definitely not a ghost

273
00:15:34,840 --> 00:15:36,360
but someone is definitely

274
00:15:36,920 --> 00:15:38,400
trying to tell us something

275
00:15:39,560 --> 00:15:40,560
Just now, didn't they

276
00:15:40,920 --> 00:15:42,720
mention some kind of village?

277
00:15:43,240 --> 00:15:44,040
What village?

278
00:15:44,800 --> 00:15:45,600
Auspicious Village
